-- Merkel, Monti Agree ‘Will Do Everything’ to Protect Euro
-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 2012-07-29T12:44:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-29/merkel-monti-agree-will-do-everything-to-protect-euro.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  and
Italian Prime Minister Mario Monti agreed that the European
Union’s summit conclusions last month must be implemented “as
quickly as possible” after speaking by phone yesterday.   Merkel and Monti “agreed that Germany and Italy will do
everything to protect the euro area,” German government
spokesman Georg Streiter said in an e-mailed statement today in
Berlin. Monti agreed to travel to Berlin for talks with Merkel
in the second half of August, Streiter said.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
